# Contributing Event Data

- Keep contributions focused and verifiable.
- Prefer one event per PR unless updates are tightly related.
- Add source context in comments (`sourceNotes`) for future maintainers.

# Add a New Event

1. Create `data/events/<event-slug>.jsonc`.
2. Fill identity, links, status, `lastUpdated`, `historicalEditions`, and `nextEdition`.
3. Include comments for non-obvious assumptions (especially estimated dates).
4. Ensure no past-only display behavior (provide a future estimate when needed).

# Update an Existing Event

- Update `status`, `nextEdition`, and any ticket fields that changed.
- Append new completed editions to `historicalEditions`.
- Refresh `lastUpdated` every time data is touched.
- Preserve existing comments that explain provenance.

# PR Conventions

- Title format: `:card_file_box: Add/Update <Event Name>`.
- Include links used for verification in the PR description.
- Mention whether dates are confirmed or estimated.
